---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(lang);

const structuredData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: t.markdown.title,
  description: t.markdown.metaDescription,
  inLanguage: 'en',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Vibe Coding with Claude',
  },
};

const readmeExample = `# My Vibe Coding Project

## 📝 Description
A personal task management web application built with vibe coding.

## 🎯 Features
- ✅ Create, edit, and delete tasks
- ⏰ Reminders and due dates  
- 📱 Responsive interface
- 💾 Local storage

## 🚀 Technologies
- HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
- LocalStorage for persistence
- Bootstrap for styling

## 📋 TODO
- [ ] Add task categories
- [ ] Export tasks to PDF
- [ ] Cloud synchronization
- [x] Responsive design ✓

## 🔧 Installation
1. Clone the repository
2. Open \`index.html\` in your browser
3. Ready to use!

## 📞 Support
If you need help, contact [your@email.com]`;

const changelogExample = `# Changelog

## [1.2.0] - 2026-02-18
### Added
- New task search functionality
- Dark/light theme toggle

### Fixed  
- Bug when editing long tasks
- Date issues in Safari

## [1.1.0] - 2026-02-15
### Added
- Email reminders
- Priority filters

### Changed
- Improved mobile interface`;

const contextExample = `# CONTEXT.md

## 🎯 Project Goal
Create a simple and effective task management application for university students.

## 👥 Target User
- Students aged 18-25
- Need to organize assignments, exams, projects
- Prefer simple and fast tools
- Primarily use mobile devices

## 🎨 Visual Style
- Minimalist and clean
- Colors: blue (#2563eb) as primary
- Typography: Inter or similar
- Icons: Heroicons or Feather

## ⚡ Technical Requirements
- Must work offline
- Fast loading (< 2 seconds)  
- Compatible with iOS Safari and Chrome
- No heavy external dependencies

## 🚫 Limitations
- No login/registration needed
- No backend required for now
- Budget: $0 (free tools only)`;
---

<ContentLayout
  title={`${t.markdown.title} | ${t.siteTitle}`}
  description={t.markdown.metaDescription}
  lang={lang}
  currentPath="markdown"
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <h1>.MD Files for Beginners</h1>
  <p class="lead">Why Markdown files are essential for efficient vibe coding</p>

  <nav class="toc">
    <h2>Contents</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#what-are">What are .MD files?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#why-important">Why are they important for Claude?</a></li>
      <li><a href="#essential-files">Essential .MD files</a></li>
      <li><a href="#best-practices">Best practices</a></li>
      <li><a href="#examples">Practical examples</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <section id="what-are">
    <h2>What are .MD files?</h2>

    <p><strong>Markdown (.md)</strong> is a lightweight markup language that allows you to format text simply using symbols like <code>#</code>, <code>*</code>, <code>-</code>, etc.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>Why Markdown?</strong> It's readable by both humans and machines. Claude can perfectly understand the content and structure of your .MD files.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Basic Markdown syntax</h3>
    
    <CodeBlock language="markdown" code={`# Main title
## Subtitle  
### Level 3 heading

**Bold text**
*Italic text*

- Bulleted list
- Second item

1. Numbered list
2. Second item

[Link](https://example.com)

\`inline code\`

\`\`\`javascript
// Code block
const message = "Hello world!";
\`\`\`

> Quote or important note`} />

    <p>With this simple syntax you can create clear and well-structured documentation.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="why-important">
    <h2>Why are they important for Claude Code?</h2>

    <p>.MD files are <strong>crucial</strong> for Claude to understand your project. They act as your application's "brain":</p>

    <div class="benefits-grid">
      <div class="benefit">
        <h3>🧠 Project context</h3>
        <p>Claude reads your .MD files to understand what you're building, for whom, and with what constraints.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="benefit">
        <h3>📋 Clear requirements</h3>
        <p>Documenting features, visual style, and technical requirements allows Claude to generate more precise code.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="benefit">
        <h3>🎯 Consistent decisions</h3>
        <p>With clear documentation, Claude makes design and architecture decisions consistent with your vision.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="benefit">
        <h3>🔄 Efficient iteration</h3>
        <p>When modifying .MD files, Claude automatically adapts the code while maintaining coherence.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-success">
      <p><strong>Golden rule:</strong> Always document before coding. 5 minutes writing a good README.md will save you hours of corrections.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="essential-files">
    <h2>Essential .MD files for your project</h2>

    <div class="file-types">
      <div class="file-type">
        <h3>📖 README.md</h3>
        <p><strong>The most important.</strong> Describes what your project does, how to install and use it.</p>
        <p><strong>Claude reads it first</strong> to understand the general context.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-type">
        <h3>📝 TODO.md</h3>
        <p>List of pending tasks, features to implement, and known bugs.</p>
        <p>Helps Claude prioritize and plan development.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-type">
        <h3>📅 CHANGELOG.md</h3>
        <p>Project change history. What was added, changed, or fixed in each version.</p>
        <p>Claude uses it to understand the project's evolution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-type">
        <h3>🎯 CONTEXT.md</h3>
        <p>Specific information about target users, constraints, design decisions.</p>
        <p>Crucial context for Claude to make the right decisions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="file-type">
        <h3>⚙️ SETUP.md</h3>
        <p>Detailed project installation and configuration instructions.</p>
        <p>Especially useful for complex projects with multiple dependencies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-practices">
    <h2>Best practices</h2>

    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip">
        <h3>✅ Be specific</h3>
        <p>Instead of "make a pretty website", write "minimalist design with blue (#2563eb) and gray (#6b7280) colors".</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <h3>📱 Mention platforms</h3>
        <p>Specify if it's web, mobile, desktop. Claude will optimize code for each platform.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <h3>👥 Describe users</h3>
        <p>Age, technical knowledge, devices they use. Claude will adapt the UX accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <h3>🚫 Include limitations</h3>
        <p>Budget, time, technologies you DON'T want to use. Avoids irrelevant proposals.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <h3>📊 Prioritize features</h3>
        <p>Mark what's essential, important, or "nice to have". Claude will focus efforts correctly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tip">
        <h3>🔄 Keep updated</h3>
        <p>.MD files should reflect the current project state. Update them regularly!</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Use emojis in your .MD titles. They not only look better, they also help Claude understand context quickly (🎯 = goal, 🚫 = limitation, etc.)</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="examples">
    <h2>Practical examples</h2>

    <h3>Example 1: Complete README.md</h3>
    <CodeBlock language="markdown" code={readmeExample} />

    <h3>Example 2: CHANGELOG.md</h3>
    <CodeBlock language="markdown" code={changelogExample} />

    <h3>Example 3: CONTEXT.md</h3>
    <CodeBlock language="markdown" code={contextExample} />

    <div class="next-steps">
      <h3>Next steps</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Create a README.md for your next project before writing code</li>
        <li>Add a TODO.md with the features you want to implement</li>
        <li>Experiment with Claude Code: you'll see the difference good documentation makes</li>
        <li>Keep your .MD files updated as the project evolves</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-success">
      <p><strong>You're ready!</strong> With this knowledge about .MD files, Claude will understand your projects much better and generate more precise and useful code.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="next-section">
      <a href="/en/openclaw" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">
        Next: OpenClaw →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ContactForm 
    showSetupService={false}
    showLeadCapture={true}
    lang="en"
  />
</ContentLayout>

<style>
  .benefits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .benefit {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .benefit h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .benefit p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .file-types {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .file-type {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }

  .file-type h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .file-type p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .file-type p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .tips-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .tip {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .tip h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .tip p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .next-steps {
    margin: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.1), rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1));
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .next-steps h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .next-steps ol {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .next-steps li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .next-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .toc {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .toc h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .toc ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .benefits-grid,
    .tips-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>